From 07b3580eb9d2d9e4e50e453c237471f5d8eb5f3c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Philippov <paul@themactep.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 21:50:44 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] SETUP fallback: search all sessions when client omits
 stream prefix

Some ONVIF clients (e.g. AgentDVR) resolve relative track control URLs
against the server root instead of the Content-Base. They send e.g.
SETUP rtsp://host/track4 instead of rtsp://host/ch0/track4.

When both standard lookups fail (empty urlPreSuffix treated as stream
name, then urlSuffix treated as stream name), iterate all
ServerMediaSessions to find one containing a subsession whose trackId
matches urlSuffix, and retry with that session.
